## Issuing a revision

1. Add an entry to the bottom of `revisions.yaml`.
[% if audience == 'regulator' %]1. Fill in `approver` and `effective_date`. The build fails without them.
[% endif %]1. Commit, then tag: `git tag v<revision> && git push --tags`.
[% if build_pdf %]1. CI builds the PDF and attaches it to a GitHub release. That release asset is
   the controlled copy -- link people to it rather than to the Read the Docs
   PDF, which is rebuilt in place and can change under them.
[% endif %]
